-- 
Hungary State Spending to Rise 3.8% Next Year, Napi Reports

-- B y   E d i t h   B a l a z s
-- 
2011-10-20T06:00:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/hungary-state-spending-to-rise-3-8-next-year-napi-reports.html
Hungary’s state budget spending will
rise by 3.8 percent next year before falling 1.2 percent in 2013
and 3.3 percent in 2014,  Napi Gazdasag  said, citing next year’s
budget draft.  State media will receive 10.4 percent more in state funding
and the government will more than double public works-related
spending in 2012, the newspaper said.  The Cabinet will cut unemployment benefits by almost half
to 68.7 billion forint ($317 million) next year to cover the
costs of public works projects, according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Edith Balazs in Budapest at 
 ebalazs1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  